M|references|- Data and original insights
M|references|- Carousel posts (doc format)
M|references|- Polls that spark discussion
M|references|**What doesn't:**
M|references|- Overly promotional cnt
M|references|- Generic motivational quotes
M|references|- Links in the main post (kills reach)
M|references|- Corporate speak without personality
M|references|**Format tips:**
M|references|- First line is everything (hook before "see more")
M|references|- Use line breaks for readability
M|references|- 1,200-1,500 characters performs well
M|references|- Put links in comments, not post body
M|references|- Tag people sparingly and genuinely
M|references|**Algorithm tips:**
M|references|- First hour engagement matters most
M|references|- Comments > reactions > clicks
M|references|- Dwell time (people reading) signals quality
M|references|- No external links in post body
M|references|- doc posts (carousels) get strong reach
M|references|- Polls drive engagement but don't build authority
